channel.description:
I believe I have all my settings correct...
[ul][li]IPs are set to 127.0.0.1 in client.java[/li] [li]Environmental Variables are set to my jkd[/li] [li]Canyouseeme.org says "Success: I can see your service on 75.***.***.*** on port (43594) Your ISP is not blocking port 43594"[/li] [li]I have a static IP set (It wont work with a dynamic or static)[/li][/ul]
I think all of these are correct right? Is anyone willing to take a look at my files through TV? If not can you please tell me what I'm doing wrong? I know it's possible to get it to work on my PC because I ran my server with no problem a week ago. And I just can't remember what it was that I changed :S It stopped working when I unplugged my laptop to bring it to a friends house so maybe it's something to do with my IP? Please help I've been at this for a week already and nobody was of any help ):
